library(readr)
library(ggstatsplot)
library(ggplot2)
library(qacr)
library(dplyr)
library(scales)
library(ggsci)
players_positions <- read_csv('data/players_positions.csv')
players_positions$hero_position <- as.factor(players_positions$hero_position)
unique(players_positions$hero_position)
## [1] supports  offlaners midlaners carry    
## Levels: carry midlaners offlaners supports
players_positions$hero_position2 <- factor(players_positions$hero_position, 
                                          levels=c('carry', 'midlaners', 'offlaners', 
                                                   'supports'))
table(players_positions$hero_position)
## 
##     carry midlaners offlaners  supports 
##    136550    111841    114526    137046
table(players_positions$hero_position2)
## 
##     carry midlaners offlaners  supports 
##    136550    111841    114526    137046
clusters <- read_csv('data/heroes_clusters_avg.csv')
clusters <-  clusters[3:13] 
clusters <- clusters %>% 
  rename(cluster = hero_cluster)
clusters <-  clusters %>% 
  mutate(cluster = recode(cluster, '0' = 'offlaners', '1' = 'carry',
                          '2' = 'midlaners', '3' = 'supports'))
cluster_res <- players_positions[2:9]
cluster_res <- cluster_res %>% 
  rename(cluster = hero_position)
new_labels <- c("hero_damage" = "hero damage", "kda" = "KDA", 
                "level" = "max level", "tower_damage" = "tower damage",
                "xp_per_min" = "XP / min", "gold_per_min" = "gold / min",
                "gold_spent" = "gold spending")

profile_plot(cluster_res, type='bar') + 
  scale_fill_npg(alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = new_labels) 

new_labels <- c("hero_damage" = "hero damage", "kda" = "KDA", 
                "level" = "max level", "mid_lane" = "middle lane presence", 
                "off_lane" = "off lane presence", "safe_lane" = "safe lane presence",
                "tower_damage" = "tower damage", "xp_per_min" = "XP / min",
                "gold_per_min" = "gold / min", "gold_spent" = "gold spending")

profile_plot(clusters, type='bar') + 
  scale_fill_npg(alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = new_labels) 

ggbetweenstats(data = clusters,
               x = cluster,
               y = gold_spent, 
               type = "nonparametric", 
               plot.type = "boxviolin",
               pairwise.comparisons = TRUE,
               pairwise.display = "significant",
               centrality.plotting = F,
               bf.message = FALSE,
               conf.level = 0.95,
               xlab = "Position",
               ylab = "Average Gold Spending", 
               package = "ggsci",
               palette = "nrc_npg") +
  theme(plot.margin = unit(c(0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5), "cm"))  # adjust the margins
